Set Up Your Data in Databricks

Access Salesforce data in your Databricks notebook using a Python connector. The user-friendly interface lets you quickly execute queries against data in Data Cloud so that you can extract the data that you need into Python.

In your Databricks notebook, install the CDP Python Connector to access Data Cloud objects and ingest Salesforce data into Databricks.
As part of the Python connector configuration, create a connected app.
Restrict access to IP addresses to manage access to your data.
Use a key-based authentication to securely access your data.
In Data Cloud, connect to your data source to query the dataset in Databricks. For example, to get email engagement data, you need access to the Email Engagement object in Marketing Cloud Engagement.
To consume the inferences in Data Cloud, upload the Python file to your notebook.
To get your model endpoint, go to the Databricks dashboard in the Registered Models - Serving section. Note the URL as you need these details to connect your model with Salesforce.
